    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-07-02T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-07-02T23:00:00-05:00" n="507"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d507">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.50 Recovery/7–348: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-07-03T13:00:00+09:00"
                            >July 3, 1948—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 3—2:43 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1221. ReDeptel 979, July 2, 7 p.m.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Re paragraph 2, impossible revise article V (see Embtel 1220, <pb
                            facs="0608" n="598" xml:id="pg_598"/> July 3, 11 a.m.). To attempt to do
                        so would postpone signing after July 3.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Re paragraph 3: <list>
                            <label>(<hi rend="italic">a</hi>)</label>
                            <item>Norm [<hi rend="italic">Term</hi>] “United States of America”
                                stricken from article IV;</item>
                            <label>(<hi rend="italic">b</hi>)</label>
                            <item>Phrase cited at end second sentence, paragraph 1, article VI
                                missing from text. Further “objectives” appear our text.</item>
                            <label>(<hi rend="italic">c</hi>)</label>
                            <item>Paragraph 7 of annex not in text, but will be handled by exchange
                                of notes to be published.</item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
